The paper focuses on the application of deep learning algorithms for human affect recognition, which involves analyzing audiovisual and physiological data. This falls under the categories of computer vision (cs.CV) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of multimodal sensor data, which could also fall under multimedia (cs.MM). The paper extensively discusses the use of deep neural networks, which is a popular topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE).
